commit.message: Bump to 0.2.2.

Fix returning Py_None with refcounting.

This effectively fixes compatibility with PyPy.
Bump PV to 0.2.1.

Add support for Python 3.

The solution is based by one implemented in pyh2o.
Move sources to src/.
Bump PV to 0.2.
Coding style.
Don't mix decls and code.
Convert to C99.

Remove (unnecessary) C++ exceptions.

We have to use Python exception handling anyway, and the C++ exceptions
don't give us any advantage.
Bump PV to 0.1.
Use const more often.
Always reset the context before performing mounts/umounts.
Add a separate method for R/W mounting.
Add copyright to main source file.
Rename the package to pymountboot, to match the module.
Replace use of subprocess.check_output() for py2.6.
Support mounting and unmounting /boot from fstab.
Support remounting /boot r/w and back r/o.
Basic API draft.
Create libmount context for our object.
Initialize the codebase.
